-- int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item (most recent first)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY status = 'approved' DESC, return_date DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join order items with deduped returns to identify returned items
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.product_id,
        CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

```sql
-- int_items_with_categories.sql
-- Enrich items with product and category information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        iwr.item_id,
        iwr.is_returned,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} iwr
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = iwr.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- fct_return_rate_by_category.sql
-- Calculate return rates by product category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        category_name,
        COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
        ROUND(CAST(SUM(is_returned) AS DECIMAL(10,4)) / COUNT(*), 4) AS return_rate
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_categories') }}
    GROUP BY category_name
)
SELECT * FROM source
